# JSDoc — almost none

Plain JS, no `@ts-check`. **Do not annotate signatures.** The code is the contract.

**Constructors and all function bodies: zero `@type`, zero `@param` — see `no-inline-type-in-constructors.mdc`.**

## Banned

- `@param` / `@returns` on functions, methods, constructors, closures — anywhere
- `@type` on locals, params, fields inside functions, constructors, loops, callbacks
- `@typedef` spam on every export; multi-line blocks that only list types
- JSDoc on obvious primitives (`/** @param {number} col */`)
- `@param {object} state` — useless everywhere

```javascript
// ❌ BANNED
/** @param {number} col @param {number} row */
export function growCellBounds(bounds, col, row) { ... }

// ❌ BANNED — inside function body
function stamp() {
    /** @type {{ col: number, row: number }[]} */
    const stamped = [];
    /** @param {number} globalCol @param {number} globalRow */
    const toLocal = (globalCol, globalRow) => { ... };
}

// ❌ BANNED — constructor / class field
constructor(grid) {
    /** @type {Map<number, Hop[]>} */
    this.hops = new Map();
}
```

## Allowed (rare)

- **One line** of prose when it explains non-obvious *why* (schema version, worker boundary, encoding quirk) — no `@` tags required
- **Module-level `@typedef`** only for shapes that cross a real boundary (snapshot JSON, public API between folders) — one typedef per concept, not per function

```javascript
// ✅ OK — why, not types
/** Portal hops are built with a Sandbox policy callback injected at sync time. */
export function buildBoundaryNavHops(grid, resolvePortalHopEntry) { ... }
```

## When adding code

- Default: **no JSDoc at all**
- If you reach for `@type` inside a function — use a plain `const` / destructuring; the name should carry meaning
- If you reach for `@param` — delete the comment block instead
- Do not "fix" missing JSDoc in files you are not otherwise changing

## Review bar

- Any `@param` or inner `@type` in the diff → remove unless user explicitly asked for it
- Comment longer than the function → delete the comment
